        <li><strong>Proximity and Temperature</strong>Because of its closeness to its star, it is exposed to intense
            radiation and can experience temperatures on its surface of up to 1,500 degrees Celsius, which practically
            removes any significant atmosphere.</li>

        <li><strong>Potential for Additional Discoveries</strong>:There may be more planets in the system than the red
            dwarf that serves as its main star, which could give more background for comprehending the genesis and
            development of USPs.</li>

        <li><strong>Scientific Interst</strong>: GJ 367b's features, such as its size and orbital period, make it a
            fascinating candidate for additional research to learn more about the dynamics of planetary systems
            surrounding M dwarf stars.​</li>
